msgid "The National Rail Service publishes a tender notice on March 15 with a submission deadline of March 20."
msgstr ""

#: ../../cli/indicators/R/003.md:19
msgid "Why is this a red flag?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../cli/indicators/R/003.md:22
msgid "A corrupt buyer can give the pre-determined bidder an unfair advantage by privately informing the pre-determined bidder of the opportunity in advance, and by giving other bidders less time to prepare competitive bids."
msgstr ""

#: ../../cli/indicators/R/003.md:25
msgid "<small>Based on \"Shortened time span for bidding process\" in [*Corruption in Public Procurement: Finding the Right Indicators*](https://www.researchgate.net/publication/303359108_Corruption_in_Public_Procurement_Finding_the_Right_Indicators), \"Short submission period\" in [*An Objective Corruption Risk Index Using Public Procurement Data*](https://www.researchgate.net/publication/301646354_An_Objective_Corruption_Risk_Index_Using_Public_Procurement_Data), \"Short or inadequate notice to bidders\" in [*Guide to Combating Corruption & Fraud in Infrastructure Development Projects*](https://guide.iacrc.org/red-flag-short-or-inadequate-notice-to-bidders/), and \"Deadline for submitting bids is very short\" in [*Fraud in Public Procurement: A collection of Red Flags and Best Practices*](https://ec.europa.eu/sfc/system/files/documents/sfc-files/fraud-public-procurement-final-20122017-ares20176254403.pdf).</small>"
